  "statement": "No spin-1/2 (as expected).  A 2pi rotation returns the field to +itself (O(2pi)=+1 for every integer angular number m); there is no 4pi double cover.  A real scalar theta carries only INTEGER angular structure -- a half-integer (which would give O(2pi)=-1) is not a single-valued function on the plane and would require a spinor field, which theta does not have.  Spin-1/2 needs internal (spinor/vector) structure ABSENT from the scalar sector; it cannot emerge from theta alone."
